AbdurRazaq Tope Balogun, Lagos State governorship aspirant on the platform of Action Alliance (AA), has declared that he is not coming on board to wrestle power from the ruling party, All Progressive Congress (APC). According to him, he is contesting for the governorship election to bring about electoral evolution and equity in the state. Balogun disclosed this on Saturday following his gubernatorial declaration of intent to contest in the 2023 general election, promising that that his administration will bring about equity into the state if he is elected as the next governor. -Advertisement- He said, “Equity is wrong with the present state government, we don’t practice equity and we lack good governors as a result of lack of equity. “I am not wresting power with APC, I am coming up with electoral evolution and we are going to take power by the ballot. By the time they vote for us massively, and we have enough votes, they will have no choice than to surrender. They have made the people of Lagos to suffer for long.”